Course Syllabus
======
Professor: <a href="https://biostatistics.massgeneral.org/faculty/brian-healy-phd/">Dr. Brian Healy</a>
<br><br>
This course is reserved for participants in the Program in Clinical Effectiveness only. Introduces basic and intermediate biostatistical techniques with an emphasis on applications to clinical research. Topics for the first half of the course include probability and statistics, hypothesis testing, confidence intervals, non-parametrics, and power calculations. Topics for the second half of the course include regression, paired and matched analyses, analysis of variance and multiple comparisons procedures.
